Abstract: /*      solve linear system with tridiagonal n by n matrix a        using Gaussian elimination *without* pivoting        where   a(i,i-1) = sub[i]  for 2<=i<=n        a(i,i)   = diag[i] for 1<=i<=n        a(i,i+1) = sup[i]  for 1<=i<=n-1        (the values sub[1], sup[n] are ignored)        right hand side vector b[1:n] is overwritten with solution        NOTE: 1...n is used in all arrays, 0 is unused */
